<reference id="linktext" xml:lang="en-us">
   <title>
      <keyword>linktext</keyword>
   </title>
   <shortdesc>The &lt;<keyword>linktext</keyword>&gt; element provides the literal
label or line of text for a link. In most cases, the text of a link can be
resolved during processing by cross reference with the target
resource. Use the &lt;<keyword>linktext</keyword>&gt; element only when the target
cannot be reached, such as when it is a peer or external link.</shortdesc>
